Preconditions:
The method should take two integer parameters: candies and numPeople.
The candies parameter should represent the total number of candies available.
The numPeople parameter should represent the number of people to distribute the candies to.
The candies parameter should be a positive integer.
The numPeople parameter should be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an array of integers.
The length of the returned array should be equal to the value of numPeople.
The sum of all elements in the returned array should be equal to the value of candies.
Each element in the returned array should represent the number of candies received by each person.
The distribution of candies should be as fair as possible, with each person receiving an equal or nearly equal number of candies.